name: Electric Badge-aloo
item_description: This badge's monocle lets you know it can't see, the cane tells you it's at death's door, and the top hat says it's rich! Marry this badge before some other gold digger snaps it up!

name: Modest Metal Pile of Scrap
item_description: This humble hat pile of one tells the world that there are more important things in life than money. Like for instance not having any.

name: Letch's LED
item_description: Comes with x-ray specs that let you see through people's clothes while alerting them with a siren and shouted warnings that you're doing it. Great for prison aficionados who want to go to jail but don't know how.

name: Galvanized Gibus
item_description: Elegant simplicity and old-world charm combine with the intoxicating aromas of methyl alcohol and gasoline. Do not wear in unventilated areas.

name: Soldered Sensei
item_description: Karate masters WANT you to think there's no belt higher than black. But what if we told you there was a secret metal belt ABOVE black that lets you kick a black belt's ass all over the place? Scared black belt guys have been trying to keep a lid on this for years.

name: Shooter's Tin Topi
item_description: This safari helmet was welded together from actual blood-spattered scraps of jeeps, rifles, shells and fillings discovered at the mauling sites of previous safaris. Wear it as a constant reminder never to do anything as stupid as go on safari.

name: Noble Nickel Amassment of Hats
item_description: Some hat towers come from humble beginnings, clawing their way to nobility one hat at a time. Other hat towers, like this one, just have rich dads who are the Chief Business Development Officer at Hewlett Packard.

name: Base Metal Billycock
item_description: Robo-impersonate your favorite fictional bowler-hatted characters, from Batman's Riddler to Clockwork Orange's Alex to England's Winston Churchill.

name: Towering Titanium Pillar of Hats
item_description: Asimov's Three Laws of Robotics state that 1. Robots can't harm humans and 2. Robots must obey humans, and 3. This hat looks great.

name: Megapixel Beard
item_description: Great for taking pictures of all the sexy make-outs you're going to have now that you've got a robot beard. If there's anything ladies find more irresistible, write in and tell us and we'll bolt it onto this perpetual make-out machine.

name: HDMI Patch
item_description: Bundled with a broad selection of eyeball-related movies ("Eyes Wide Shut", "The Hills Have Eyes, Part II" and three more) that your friends can enjoy from the comfort of your face.

name: Bolted Bombardier
item_description: Remember that time you met the wisest robot in the world? And tore his beard off and stole his stupid pipe? Because the police are here and they want to talk to you.

name: Titanium Towel
item_description: Sure, regular towels work fine for water, but what if you're covered in magnets? What's your regular towel doing for you now? Watching you slowly die of magnetism, that's what.

name: Gridiron Guardian
item_description: This helmet commemorates the epic Canadian Robot Football League showdown between Les Montreal Footballiers and their Manitoban rivals the Winnepeg Saskatchewans. Don't believe us? Ask any Canadian!

name: Tyrantium Helmet
item_description: This hat kicks your ass so hard you'll fly into an alternate dimension where Vikings are robots. Deal with it!

name: Battery Canteens
item_description: Don't let the name fool you: These aren't actual battery canteens capable of converting stored chemical energy into electrical energy. They're just regular canteens that look identical to your water canteen and are filled with battery acid.

name: FR-0
item_description: Own this one-of-a-kind piece of memorabilia from the classic '70s film "Blaxton Hale vs. Black HAL 9000".

name: Steel Shako
item_description: Combining the sublime pageantry of Tchaikovsky's "Nutcracker" with the bold futurism of Tchaikovsky's "Robot Nutcracker vs. Tarzan".

name: Bot Dogger
item_description: It's inevitable that robot hot dog hats will someday become the most popular fashion accessory on the planet. And when they do, everyone will claim they liked them "before they were cool." Thanks to the Bot Dogger, only YOU will be able to prove it.

name: Ye Oiled Baker Boy
item_description: It's as if this hat fell off the tiny metal head of a dirt-stained urchinbot selling robonewspapers in 1899 Mecha-London, rolled through a time tunnel and into your modern backpack.

name: Scrap Sack
item_description: Concerned about your many stalkers going through your garbage while you're at work? Rest easy with the Scrap Sack, which lets you keep an eye on your secret-filled trash at all times.

name: Pure Tin Capotain
item_description: Witch-hunting: necessary, but time-consuming. What if we told you you could burn up to five witches a day without lifting a finger? Introducing the Pure Tin Capotain, the greatest time-saving invention since the electric can opener.

name: Plumber's Pipe
item_description: Learn plumbing by osmosis with this handy Home Plumber's Kit! Comes with pipe, length of wire.

name: Teddy Robobelt
item_description: This tiny robotic bear used to be the President. Now he lives in your pocket. How could the mighty have fallen so far? [makes drinking gesture] Glug glug wink wink.

name: Cyborg Stunt Helmet
item_description: If you pause that big fight scene in the classic film "Swinging Fists of Future Hercules", you can tell that's not actually famous robot actor Kirk RoboDouglas, but a cyborg stuntman. Support the unsung heroes of the silver-plated screen with this limited edition stunt helmet.

name: Electric Escorter
item_description: "And it seems to me you lived your life / with a lightbulb in your head / wishing you had cleaned the hole / as the cephalic tetanus spread."  Elton John (words by Bernie Taupin)

name: Full Metal Drill Hat
item_description: What is your major malfunction, Private Robot? You had best defrag yourself or I will unscrew your head, access the CPU in your neck and fix your major malfunction!

name: Bolt Boy
item_description: That item was originally a make-believe superhero accessory tie-in to an imaginary soft drink enjoyed by a fictional character. Now it's also made of metal. There are so many layers of abstraction going on here even we don't know what to make of it.

name: Metal Slug
item_description: They came from outer space. And they came to conquer. It was the perfect space crime. But there's just one problem. YOU. "The Metal Slug". Rated R. This Friday. On your HEAD.

name: Broadband Bonnet
item_description: This brimless bonnet cap comes equipped with a satellite pom-pom that streams up-to-the-minute news relevant to the on-the-go Scotsman (golf scores, whiskey prices, when "Braveheart" is on).

name: Bonk Leadwear
item_description: In 1792, Italian physicist Alessandro Volta invented the battery by mixing zinc, ammonium chloride and molten salt together. In 1932, American soft drink magnate Theophilus Bonk added sugar to this mixture and invented Bonk Cola.

name: Plug-In Prospector
item_description: Robo-future history comes alive! Pretend you're a grizzled, cantankerous robot prospector, drunk on teeny-tiny shots of nano-whiskey in the Olllld Cyber-West during the Great Battery Rush of 3047.

name: Rusty Reaper
item_description: Are you the personification of death? Do you need to spraypaint something indoors? This skull-shaped rebreather has you covered.

name: Soldier's Sparkplug
item_description: Sometimes a cigar is just a cigar. Other times it is a sparkplug. Sometimes it is a boot. The important thing is that you have something in your mouth that is on fire.

name: Bolted Bicorne
item_description: One little-known fact about parrots: They WILL peck a hole through a human pirate skull. But they can't peck through solid steel. And if they try? This baby's electrified to the tune of 10,000 volts. Your move, parrots.

name: Timeless Topper
item_description: Most hats are made of felt, canvas or other non-durable cloths that decompose after a mere 10,000 years. The Timeless Topper's built for the long haul, with an outer layer of scrap titanium and an inner core of plastic bags, foam cups and disposable diapers.

name: Filamental
item_description: Is your Pyro made up of alternating current or direct current? Only your electrician knows for sure!

name: Strontium Stove Pipe
item_description: Beep boop! I am Old Railsplitter! Welcome to the Hall of Robopresidents! I did my homework on the back of a shovel! Now I must kill all humans with a shovel because I just now became sentient! Beep boop kill all humans!

name: Firewall Helmet
item_description: Learn the secret that firefighters guard fiercely: There is no better hat to wear while entering a burning building than a metal hat. Why? The metal will absorb 100% of the heat, leaving your bare skin cool and refreshed, probably.

name: Respectless Robo-Glove
item_description: When that robot selflessly gave you its hand, it assumed you'd study it to advance the field of prosthetic medicine. Sucker. Hey, everybody check me out! I'm a metal chicken! Beep beep gobble boop!

name: Pyro's Boron Beanie
item_description: Friends and loved ones will call you stupid for wearing this hat. "Hey, moron!" your mother will say. But they won't think it's so funny when you win the Backwards Swimming competition at the Olympics, and are later stripped of your medal for cheating.

name: Halogen Head Lamp
item_description: This medical marvel improves on the obsolete doctor's head mirror by replacing the mirror part with a 10,000 watt lamp part that can be seen from space. Peer inside your patients' disease-riddled ears, noses and throats from a safe distance.

name: Platinum Pickelhaube
item_description: Invented by Nikolai Tesla in any one of his ten million appearances in crappy steampunk fiction, probably.

name: Virus Doctor
item_description: Whether you're a 17th century plague doctor, a professional wrestler, or a waiter at a plague-themed family restaurant, this hat lets you look the part while delivering last rites, a Tombstone Piledriver and/or plate after plate of bacon-wrapped jalapeo poppers.

name: Texas Tin-Gallon
item_description: It's a historical fact that in cowboy times, cloth was hard to come by. Creative cowpokes kept the sun out of their eyes by making hats out of what they had in abundance: sheet-metal trees and bolt cactuses.

name: Titanium Tyrolean
item_description: Meet the robot apocalypse in style with this puckish number, perfect for infiltrating the sentient mother computer located in the Swiss pavilion at Epcot Center.

name: Practitioner's Processing Mask
item_description: Fact: 70% of the air you breathe was recently in someone's butt. This handy contraption runs the farty air you live in through a gauntlet of soapy water and potpourri before entering your body.

name: Bootleg Base Metal Billycock
item_description: Trick your friends into thinking your enormous metal hat is a smaller, different hat. If this was actually illegal it would be the PERFECT CRIME.

name: Mecha-Medes
item_description: Mecha-Medes first appeared in Archimedes' Flights of Fantasy #314 when Archimedes accidentally fell off a table into a parallel world, met his robot double, ate some seeds, squawked in terror at a half-buried Statue of Liberty, then flew into a patio door.

name: Tungsten Toque
item_description: Commemorate history's greatest robot Canadians with this knitted steel cap. Former Prime Minister Pierre Trudeau! Optimus Prime Minister! Commander Data from the hit CBC drama Deep Space Prince Edward Island!

name: Steam Pipe
item_description: Just like steampunk ruined reading, the steampipe destroys the harmless pleasure of smoking by tarting it up with a lot of bolts and dials and Nikolai Teslas. Comes with period-appropriate Gary Oldman Dracula glasses!

name: Data Mining Light
item_description: If you're a rugged coal miner like us, you know the value of throwing away your mining equipment and mining in the nude so people know how tough you are. Finally there's a version for the office worker to not wear while nudely analyzing spreadsheets.

name: Byte'd Beak
item_description: This 17th century plague mask has been upgraded for modern day masquerade-style sex parties with a built-in camera, night vision (for dimly-lit sex parties!) and state-of-the-art sex detection radar.

name: Googol Glass Eyes
item_description: These digital eye implants will let you check the weather, monitor the stock market and look up cures for infection caused by jamming unclean hunks of metal into your eye sockets.

name: Bunsen Brave
item_description: Scientists have long been baffled by the seamless metal construction of Native American grass houses and wigwams. The secret? Native Americans were filled with gasoline, and could reach a welding flame temperature of 3100 C.

name: Scrumpy Strongbox
item_description: This nitrogen-cooled liquor locker can only be opened by punching in its constantly evolving polyalphabetic stream cipher, or with the big metal key scotch taped to the bottom.

name: Dual-Core Devil Doll
item_description: These pint-sized pain proxies combine the erotic mysticism of Haitian voodoo with the stultifying boredom of math.

name: Bolted Birdcage
item_description: You love the hard-hitting Robin Williams/Nathan Lane bird prison drama "The Birdcage" so much you wish you could be thinking about it all the time. The problem: Life's many distractions. The solution: This.

name: Crosslinker's Coil
item_description: Did you know: before the mercenary fashion world discovered the obvious style and mental health benefits of wearing 22 feet of powered electrical cable around your head, people once wore hatbands made from 'silk' or other barely-lethal textiles! Strange but true.

name: Beastly Bonnet
item_description: This ceremonial headdress tells your enemies that you have the heart of a lion, the strength of a bear, the speed of a cheetah, and the rotting head of a cheetah.

name: Cheet Sheet
item_description: This cheetah-print skirt intimidates on the battlefield while allowing for freedom of movement. Let's be honest, it doesn't do a bad job of showing off those man-curves either.

name: Tartantaloons
item_description: Are these Scottish pantaloons historically accurate? You got us. Why don't you go ask your boyfriend History?

name: Steel Sixpack
item_description: This wrought-iron cuirass has been exactingly molded from the imaginary muscles you wish you had.

name: Centurion
item_description: Unlike those cheap knock-offs, the brush part of THIS centurion helmet is made from the HEAD hair of your fallen enemies.

name: Tartan Shade
item_description: This patterned cloak lets you skulk undetected in any plaid-covered shadows.

name: Hardy Laurel
item_description: This bundle of spray painted sticks signified that you were a philosopher king in primitive cultures like Ancient Rome and present-day Canada. (Equips Romevision in Mann vs. Machine mode.)

name: Brotherhood of Arms
item_description: Straight outta 2Fort.

name: Well-Rounded Rifleman
item_description: The smooth lines of this versatile number will be instantly vaguely familiar to anyone who's ever seen a train conductor, been arrested in France, or fought in the U.S. Civil War.

name: Breakneck Baggies
item_description: Combining the comfort of pajamas with the genital-concealing subterfuge of pants, these aerodynamic trackies will let your enemies know you're a man of mystery who probably got a good night's sleep.

name: Powdered Practitioner
item_description: An integral part of any travel survival kit, this wig will help you escape Disney World if the Hall of Presidents ever comes to life. Comes with tri-corn hat in case Pirates of the Caribbean comes to life instead.

name: Pocket Pyro
item_description: Loneliness is the world's deadliest silent killer. Next to carbon monoxide. But cuddle up to this adorable firebug, hold your breath, and you'll be free to concentrate on loud killers like car crashes and Freddy Krueger.

name: Cloud Crasher
item_description: This paratrooper's helmet keeps your head safe while you jump out of planes. Show those birds who's boss! Teach some fluffy little clouds what they'll get if you ever catch them around your sky again!

name: Pom-Pommed Provocateur
item_description: The thick woolen pom-pom stitched to the top of this ski mask is filled with poison, in case you are captured by people who want information on why you look ridiculous.

name: Dark Age Defender
item_description: This knight's armor will repel anything someone from the 12th century might throw at you, be it a rock, a sword, a thatched cottage or a Merlin.

name: Tyurtlenek
item_description: Around the skinny neck of an intellectual, jewel thief or Frenchman, a turtleneck tells people: "Please open-hand slap me in the face." On the iron frame of the Heavy, it says only: "I wear what I want."

name: Mair Mask
item_description: Comes with a full can of MAIR, Mann Co.'s air substitute! One part nitrogen, no parts oxygen, NINE parts electrolytesMair gives regular air a kick in the pants for manly lungs on the go.

name: Bigg Mann on Campus
item_description: "I should put a big red A on this thing for 'ALL SPORTS', cause that's my specialty."

name: Cool Cat Cardigan
item_description: "Boom! Now I'm in the fifties! I look good in ANY decade!"

name: Greased Lightning
item_description: "I'm the only one on this team not balding! Damn right I'm gonna make my hair look good!"

name: Red Army Robin
item_description: "Is tiny bird. Is adorable. TELL BIRD HE IS PRETTY!"

name: Heavy-Weight Champ
item_description: "This belt tells babies that Heavy is champ. Big belt champ of all time."

name: Tsarboosh
item_description: "Does little hat make Heavy's head look big? TELL TRUTH."

name: Glasgow Great Helm
item_description: This knight's helm is perfect for defending against 12th century offensive weaponry, like swords, sticks and definitely-not-bullets.

name: Caffeine Cooler
item_description: "Each canna Bonk's got four thousand percent of the daily caffeine a body needs, so you KNOW it's good for ya. And I drink 'em by the case, so I'm extra healthy."

name: Half-Pipe Hurdler
item_description: "My moves are SICK, brother. Ask your girlfriend, cause she's been watchin'. Don't blame her, she's only human."

name: Macho Mann
item_description: Sometimes it really does take a village, people.

name: Trash Toter
item_description: "Waste not, want not, son."

name: Dry Gulch Gulp
item_description: "When I'm hungry, I eat. When I'm thirsty, I drink. And when a man needs killin', I oblige him."

name: El Muchacho
item_description: Cosplay as a sleepy cowboy with this authentic 19th century sleeveless fleece snuggie.

name: Backpack Broiler
item_description: I've got your back... steaks.

name: Burning Bandana
item_description: Time to clean house.

name: Soot Suit
item_description: Business up front. Ten deadly gallons of pressurized gas in the back.

name: Hive Minder
item_description: The leading cause of death on the battlefield? You guessed it: Bee stings.

name: Katyusha
item_description: "Heavy does not need plane to crush you. Only fists and hat."

name: Das Hazmattenhatten
item_description: "Breathing is agreeable to me, but sometimes there is air-stench. Now I laugh in the face of air. Thank you, this hat." (Description translated from German.)

name: Das Feelinbeterbager
item_description: "Hello, men of war! You will be dead soon. Here are pills." (Description translated from German.)

name: Das Ubersternmann
item_description: "You are not important but I am. My hat is a secret hat." (Description translated from German.)

name: Das Metalmeatencasen
item_description: "There is strength in your steel breast-blouse. Your chest meat is at ease." (Description translated from German.)

name: Pardner's Pompadour
item_description: "It takes a hard man to tame this ten-gallon Texas hair tornado."

name: Birdman of Australiacatraz
item_description: "Watch like an eagle. Strike like a hawk. Dance like no one's watching."

name: Cobber Chameleon
item_description: "This little fellah's the perfect snipin' companion. He's quiet, he's camouflaged, and if you get hungry, you can eat 'im."

name: Falconer
item_description: "This falconer's glove's perfect for snipin'. It's sturdy, it's comfortable, and if a falcon lands on it, you can eat 'im."

name: Graybanns
item_description: Gray Mann might be a heartless villain. But he DOES make some sweet sunglasses. Hate the player, not the game.

name: Black Watch
item_description: This Scottish infantry tam o'shanter commemorates the desperately sober 5th batallion, who tried to make liquor out of gunpowder and accidentally invented sticky bombs.

name: Tartan Spartan
item_description: "Lads, tonight we DRINK IN HELL! And it's only noon right now, so let's ALSO DRINK RIGHT HERE!"

name: Gaelic Golf Bag
item_description: "Ach, t'is a Cinderella story! Outta nowhere. A former demolitions expert, now, about to become the Masters champion. It looks like a mirac... It's in the hole! It's in the bloody hole!"

name: Borscht Belt
item_description: "So many little pouches. Now Heavy can help carry your itty-bitty baby guns."

name: Das Naggenvatcher
item_description: "In the center of your head lives a skeleton. It is not enough! This hat is a head-skeleton for the outside." (Description translated from German.)

name: Whiskey Bib
item_description: "Sometimes when yer swiggin' woodgrain alcohol from a clay jug, a wee bit can miss the mouth, like. Catch those precious drops with a genuine Scottish whiskey bib."

name: Stormin' Norman
item_description: This knight's helm was painstakingly recreated using stills from the classic time travel episode (Ep 417: "A K.I.T.T. in King Arthur's Court") of the hit TV show Knight Rider.

name: Flared Frontiersman
item_description: "I'll tell you what, these wide-bottom pants're slick as a whistle."

name: Valley Forge
item_description: This tricorn is a tribute to our country's greatest President. The tiny medal on it is a tribute to the ribbony children's medal he won for inventing America.

name: Compatriot
item_description: "This is not a bird, maggot! It is a shoulder-mounted symbol of freedom, and you WILL salute it in this man's army!"

name: Caribbean Conqueror
item_description: "You! Stop jibbing that mainsail and give me twenty! You up in the crow's nest! Drop that telescope and get on your face! Everybody on this ship start doing push-ups!"

name: Colonial Clogs
item_description: "I can confirm that these are George Washington's actual shoes, because I found them buried two feet up an Englishman's ass!"

name: Whirly Warrior
item_description: "To your left, some French buildings. Directly in front of us is the Eiffel Tower, which I'm about to bring down. This concludes our helicopter tour of France."

name: Federal Casemaker
item_description: "Men, if we are going to take down Al Capone, we will need to be in the FBI. Step one: These hats."

name: Rebel Rouser
item_description: "Hold on, why are Americans fighting other Americans? Did everybody in France die and nobody told me?"

name: Das Maddendoktor
item_description: "My laughter is not borne from joy! I have birthed a devil! It is acceptable to me!" (Description translated from German.)

name: Bear Necessities
item_description: "In Siberia, bear try to attack family. He try this once. Now he is little hat."

name: Harmburg
item_description: "How do I look in this hat? On a scale of 'Handsome' to 'Extremely Handsome'."

name: Gaelic Garb
item_description: "And we'll tell our enemies that they may take our lives, but they'll never take our FREEDOM! To wear these POOFY SHIRTS! What's that, Havish? Oh. AND THESE SASHES!"

name: Rogue's Brogues
item_description: "Every day, I know I will be cutting something. Some days it is a rug. For those days, I have these shoes."

name: Shogun's Shoulder Guard
item_description: "The next time some bleeding heart cries on your shoulder about the state of the environment, he can slam his tear ducts into the Shogun. This shoulder is CLOSED!"

name: Das Gutenkutteharen
item_description: "The hairs on your head-skin are physically attractive. Now we should have love relations." (Description translated from German.)

name: Belgian Detective
item_description: "Inspector, seal the door! Someone in this room is a MURDERER!" [pause] "Me!" [stab stab stab stab stab]

name: Hornblower
item_description: "This uniform was worn by Horatio Nelson during the Napoleonic Wars! If you sunk his ship he would swim at you with a cannon on his back! If he ran out of cannonballs he would fire himself at your hull! That is how bad he wanted to beat the French!"

name: Lieutenant Bites
item_description: Hobbies: contracting rabies, giving people rabies. Favorite foods: spoiled sour cream rations, arm meat.

name: Brawling Buccaneer
item_description: "We do not plunder in this man's pirate army, maggot! On this ship you will patrol the seas for liberals and Communists, and go to bed at a sensible hour!"

name: Blood Banker
item_description: "Oh, you'd like to make a deposit? Allow me to make one first. One knife. Into your back."

name: After Dark
item_description: "Bartender. Scotch, neat. It has been a long day. Oh, is that a piano?" [sound of Chopin's Impromptu no. 4 in C sharp minor, ladies swooning]

name: Delinquent's Down Vest
item_description: "Boom! Look how puffy this vest is, dummy! I sent the last one back. Not. Puffy. Enough."

name: Wet Works
item_description: "Rain: It's nature's Jarate. But it's not a drama: Keep the filthy stuff off yer noggin with this rubber hat."

name: Baron von Havenaplane
item_description: "Are you a plane-driver? I cannot tell because of your hat-disguise." (Description translated from German.)

name: Das Fantzipantzen
item_description: "Fancy men are beautiful but weak! You are a strong filthy idiot. Take what is rightfully yours!" (Description translated from German.)

name: Bolshevik Biker
item_description: "I am riding to your tiny town."

name: Pampered Pyro
item_description: Today, it's YOU Fortress. You deserve it.

name: Virtual Viewfinder
item_description: Get a migraine for charity. (99 percent of community revenue goes to fund SpecialEffect, a charity working to help disabled players get back into the game.)

name: Gabe Glasses
item_description: "These glasses help Heavy read sad stupid poem on your tombstone."

name: Founding Father
item_description: This shirt envisions a terrifying alternate universe where our nation's patriots wore frilly-cuffed silk blouses instead of the respectable undershirts they possessed in actual history.

name: Bone Dome
item_description: Comes with a visor capable of shielding your eyes from the harsh glare of people running away from you on fire.

name: Air Raider
item_description: Designed specifically for hotshot pilots, this mask only distributes oxygen if you're doing a cool barrel roll into the Danger Zone.

name: Viking Braider
item_description: O.G. Vikings know: Braid before blade, son.

name: Cuban Bristle Crisis
